@Quilford and silavor: In a previous post, Duplicity said this: <blockquote><div><cite>Duplicity wrote:</cite>I'm going to attempt to do something different this game. I'll state a read that I currently have at the end of of each of my posts, the person who posts after me has to state agreement, disagreement or indifference with the read with reasoning provided.</div></blockquote>
I believe that this means that we are to respond to the statement that he makes with agreement, disagreement, or indifference.<br>
<br>
My read on Slaxx is null for the present, thus I'm indifferent on the statement that he is town.  Nintendoaddict1 strikes me as townie who is ignorant of how the strategy of mafia on this site works, but he does seem to know what the roles are and what they do.  He (nintendoaddict1) could also be scum who is ignorant of how to play strategically as scum because he said that on nSider the game was luck-based.  If he is scum, it should be plain to us later, so I suggest that we start by focusing our attention elsewhere while still keeping an eye out for something that gives him away.  Akira doesn't strike me as town or scum just yet because the wagon started due to freaky upside down typing.<br>
<br>
@Pine, what's your take on Akira's wagon, nintendoaddict1's comments, and Duplicity's way of starting the game?

@Duplicity - My post did link him to the guide. I may not have been the first, but I am sure even yourself would encourage him to take a look at it. Also, my vote was in the RVS. The vote wasn't completely random: E_Lou based his on a past game, I based mine on Nintendo's previous vote. It was as random as you can get without drawing names out of a hat.<br>
<br>
How do you feel about Quilford's actions?

@nintendo: I think most new players (or players new to this format or site) act scummy. That makes early reads of them unreliable. The best way to get reliable reads from them is to force them to grow up in a hurry, so you can get good reads from them. It's done wonders with you.<br>
<br>
<div style="display:inline;font-weight:bold">V/LA until Sunday afternoon</div>

@nintendo - Take a look at yourself. I posted a longer post not too long ago. You posted a couple of one liners and a picture this page.<br>
<br>
@Pine - I understand that it has been site wide, but you have the time to post comments like this without having the time to post anything truly useful. You have one post that sounds like it - "Scumhunter wagon needs more votes." Sounds like it to me.

I wouldn't listen to my partners advice anyways, even if they were telling me to "SHUT THE FUCK UP". But whatever makes you realize I'm town is okay by me.<br>
<br>
@Silavor, interesting point on slaxx. I don't want to lynch him today. But defenitely something we can keep in mind for future days.

@Slaxx: True, Emp is a suspect of mine, but nintendo's line of questioning is plain wrong.<br>
<br>
Not sure what to think of Ion's response, it sounds pretty honest to me, but I'm going to wait for confirmation. This is my first Mini Normal and these kind of situations are new to me.

@Mogri: Regarding the "buddying" following my reversal on Scumhunter, that's what I do. I tend to pressure my strong reads until they either flip scum or there's a good reason to suspect otherwise. SH is the rare case where he managed to change my mind and I now consider him near-confirmed-Town. Hence why I now am liking him.<br>
<br>
Otherwise, fairly good analysis. I'll have to go over it with a fine-toothed comb later, headed out on a date in a few minutes.
